The paper deals with the properties of plane straight-line graphs, which are commonly studied in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem of finding the maximum angle ϕ for a certain class of graphs on a set of points is a combinatorial optimization problem, which is often studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the analysis of the structure of graphs, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.DS, cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the results, such as in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
